          "reason": "The proposed edit removes the first occurrence of `firewall` (level 10, cost 25) and `honeypot` (level 12, cost 30) from TerminalParser.cs — these are the definitions that **exactly match** the server's Command.kt (line 56-58). After removal, only the duplicate definitions at lines 160-166 remain (`firewall` level 5/cost 8, `honeypot` level 12/cost 15), which **do not match** the server values. This breaks client-server alignment established in Phase 1.3 (FR-001), is scope creep (task 3.1 is about connecting game systems, not modifying command definitions), and the remaining duplicates would show incorrect level requirements (firewall displayed as level 5 when server requires level 10) and incorrect CPU costs."
