          "reason": "The edit targets `TutorialSystem.cs`, which is outside the declared scope for active task 3.1 (scope declared 4 files: WorldNodeSystem.cs, IPv4WorldManager.cs, GameManager.cs, TerminalParser.cs). This exact bug (await in non-async method in TutorialSystem.cs) was already cited in a prior rejection (denial history item 2, oversight sequence 5) as unplanned scope expansion. While the edit is technically correct (the method uses `await` on line 133 and requires `async`), the architect has been warned repeatedly about scope creep and is attempting to fix a bug in a completed task (2.1) outside the current task's declared scope. This violates Rule 4 (Scope Containment)."
